        "body":"<div id=\"block-52825225e4b0f37bee4ff5b5\" class=\"block is-summary\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-11-12T17:04:09.394Z\">5.04pm <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <h2 class=\"block-title\">Summary</h2> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Here is a summary of key events:</p> <p>• <strong>Charles Farr, the director-general of the Office for Security and Counter-terrorism at the Home Office, has said he learned new things about specific GCHQ operations from the Guardian’s revelations based on Edward Snowden’s leaks. He said he also learned new things about the NSA.</strong></p> <p><strong>•&nbsp;Farr, speaking to the Commons home affairs select committee,&nbsp;said the information &quot;stolen&quot; by Snowden reveals capabilities the UK has and made them less effective - &quot;there is no doubt about that&quot;.</strong> But he would not provide evidence, saying to do so would make a bad situation worse.</p> <p>• <strong>Farr said the fact an NSA contractor such as Snowden could access GCHQ documents was “an issue” and the heads of MI5, MI6 and GCHQ were responsible for dealing with that.</strong></p> <p><strong>• Farr denied that GCHQ was collecting the exact same data that the government had called for in the (now stalled) communications data bill.</strong> But when pressed he said: “Of course they do ... collect communications and communications data. My point was specifically about the UK and the data we were seeking to obtain through legislation.” He said that bill should still be brought back and made law.</p> <p><strong>• He said he completely agreed that the intelligence agencies needed to be more transparent.&nbsp;</strong></p> <p><strong>•&nbsp;David Anderson QC, the UK’s reviewer of terrorism legislation, told the&nbsp;committee&nbsp;the powers of surveillance over the security services set down in the Regulation of Investigatory Powers Act 2000 may now be out of date.&nbsp;</strong></p> <p>• <strong>Anderson said the debate over surveillance prompted by the Guardian’s Edward Snowden stories had been a useful one, but he said it was not for him to say whether the damage caused by the revelations had outweighed this.</strong>Pressed on whether he had seen any evidence of such damage, he said he had not. But he said the idea terrorists might alter their methods of communication following the stories &quot;might even be thought to be self-evident&quot;.</p> <p>• <strong>He said the debate over surveillance has been muted in the UK because thanks to &quot;Bletchley Park and 007&quot; Britons are proud of their security services.</strong> They have not had the sort of bad experience with intelligence services people had in eastern Europe or Nazi Germany, Anderson said.</p> <p>• <strong>Anderson suggested changes to schedule 7 of the Terrorism Act – which was used to detain former Guardian journalist Glenn Greenwald’s partner David Miranda –&nbsp;to stop detention without suspicion.</strong> But a “no-suspicion” rule should remain in place for stopping and examining people at ports under this power.</p> <p>That’s it from me for today, but Guardian reporters who have been closely involved in the Snowden stories will answer readers' questions via<a href=\"http://www.twitter.com/guardianUS\"> @GuardianUS</a> today from 1-2pm EST (6-7 BST). Our panel will include senior correspondent Ewen MacAskill (<a href=\"https://twitter.com/ewenmacaskill\">@ewenmacaskill</a>), who met up with Snowden in Hong Kong, US national security editor Spencer Ackerman (<a href=\"https://twitter.com/attackerman\">@attackerman</a>), special projects editor James Ball (<a href=\"https://twitter.com/jamesrbuk\">@jamesrbuk</a>) and diplomatic editor Julian Borger (<a href=\"https://twitter.com/julianborger\">@julianborger</a>). Share your questions by tweeting with the hashtag<a href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23mynsaquestion&amp;src=typd\"> #myNSAquestion</a>, and our reporters will tweet you directly with an answer. <a href=\"http://www.theguardian.com/world/2013/nov/12/nsa-discuss-snowden-revelations-guardian-reporters\">Click here for the full details</a>.</p> </div> <p class=\"block-time updated-time\">Updated <time datetime=\"2013-11-12T17:20:14.591Z\">at 5.20pm GMT</time></p> </div> <div id=\"block-52825f7de4b0f37bee4ff5ca\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-11-12T17:04:02.714Z\">5.04pm <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>The session closes.&nbsp;</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-52825cede4b07aa4168b4ac1\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-11-12T16:54:38.562Z\">4.54pm <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Austin asks how responsibly the Guardian acted in handling the Snowden information. He asks about deputy national security adviser Oliver Robbins's criticisms of the paper.</p> <p>Farr says he wants to answer in a broader way because of the Miranda case. The exposure of the information &quot;stolen&quot; by Snowden reveals capabilities we have and makes them less effective - &quot;there is no doubt about that&quot;.</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-52825ccae4b07aa4168b4ac0\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-11-12T16:52:57.952Z\">4.52pm <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Austin asks Farr if the security services would stop looking at terrorism suspects and start looking at innocent people's emails.&nbsp;</p> <p>Farr says he couldn't agree more.</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-52825c49e4b0f37bee4ff5c8\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-11-12T16:50:51.300Z\">4.50pm <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Should we be wary about working with the US if they are so lax with data as to allow a contractor (Snowden) to access GCHQ data?</p> <p>Clearly it is an issue and the spy chiefs are responsible for dealing with it, Farr says.</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-52825b99e4b0f37bee4ff5c7\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-11-12T16:50:08.588Z\">4.50pm <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Huppert asks if Farr had learned anything about the UK security services in the Guardian.</p> <p>Farr says he learned things that were new about specific GCHQ operations but he did not need to know about them.&nbsp;</p> <p>Huppert challenges him about what he said about the communications data bill. Farr says:</p> <blockquote class=\"quoted\"> <p>GCHQ has never and will never collect ..., the communications data required by law enforcement ... which we were seeking to provide for in the communications data legislation.&nbsp;</p> <p>Of course they do ... collect communications and communications data. My point was specifically about the UK and the data we were seeking to obtain through legislation. GCHQ cannot provide that data itself.</p> </blockquote> <p>Huppert tries to pin him down, and Farr says they are getting into a level of detail he is not comfortable with in public.&nbsp;</p> </div> <p class=\"block-time updated-time\">Updated <time datetime=\"2013-11-12T17:25:19.613Z\">at 5.25pm GMT</time></p> </div> <div id=\"block-52825b43e4b0f37bee4ff5c6\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-11-12T16:47:10.951Z\">4.47pm <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>The Guardian and American papers do not want to aid and abet terrorism, Winnick says.</p> <p>Farr says he did not mean to suggest that - but the effect may be to help terrorists.</p> <p>Winnick says there's no evidence.</p> <p>Farr says he won't be drawn on the evidence - putting that in the public domain would make the situation even more difficult. </p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-52825aefe4b07aa4168b4abe\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-11-12T16:45:37.160Z\">4.45pm <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Winnick says John Kerry was asked about Snowden and he said Obama was carrying out a wide review - that wouldn't have happened without Snowden, would it?</p> <p>Farr says the legal provision for the NSA and GCHQ are &quot;completely different&quot;. One should be careful about drawing analogies between the two, he says.&nbsp;</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-52825aa9e4b0f37bee4ff5c5\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-11-12T16:44:23.790Z\">4.44pm <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Winnick says former heads of MI5 and GCHQ have said since the revelations that the intelligence agencies need to be more transparent.&nbsp;</p> <p>Farr says in many ways he &quot;completely agrees&quot; but there is a difference between effective oversight and the publication of stories that damage national security.</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-52825a85e4b07aa4168b4abd\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-11-12T16:43:17.341Z\">4.43pm <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Winnick asks about the story about Merkel's phone being hacked - did finding out about that help the terrorists?</p> <p>Farr says he doesn't want to comment on NSA matters.&nbsp;</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-52825a6fe4b0f37bee4ff5c4\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-11-12T16:42:43.305Z\">4.42pm <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>That didn't come to him through the usual channels? No, and nor would I expect it to, Farr says.</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-52825a48e4b07aa4168b4abc\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-11-12T16:42:18.216Z\">4.42pm <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Did Farr discover anything in the Guardian that he didn't already know about? Farr says:</p> <blockquote class=\"quoted\"> <p>There was material in the Guardian about NSA that was completely new to me.</p> </blockquote> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-52825929e4b0f37bee4ff5c3\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-11-12T16:41:38.684Z\">4.41pm <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Ellis asks about the communications data bill. Does Farr still feel such collection of data is necessary?</p> <p>Yes, it's necessary for any crime being committed over the internet, Farr says. The legislation is still necessary, he says, and the home secretary agrees.</p> <p>Farr says he knows it has been claimed that GCHQ programmes exposed by Snowden &quot;allegedly indicate&quot; GCHQ are collecting all the data that the bill would have allowed police to have collected.</p> <blockquote class=\"quoted\"> <p>That is not the case. It's incorrect. GCHQ has never collected the data required by law enforcement ... and it never would, it's never been considered.</p> </blockquote> <p>So, he says, GCHQ's capabilities are not a substitute for the powers of the communications data bill.</p> <p>Does he agree with what the spy chiefs said about the dangers created by the Guardian's revelations? He says he agrees with everything they have said.</p> <p>Snowden and others have made the techniques used less effective. It's factually wrong that terrorists knew all this already, Farr says.&nbsp;</p> <p>He says he is completely satisfied about this - as well as terrorists other &quot;bad people&quot; are &quot;rubbing their hands with glee as well&quot;.</p> </div> <p class=\"block-time updated-time\">Updated <time datetime=\"2013-11-12T17:23:40.504Z\">at 5.23pm GMT</time></p> </div> <div id=\"block-528258f4e4b0f37bee4ff5c2\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-11-12T16:36:15.743Z\">4.36pm <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>The &quot;usual&quot; age profile for terrorists of 19-30 is the same for those travelling to Syria, Farr says.&nbsp;</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-528258c9e4b0f37bee4ff5c0\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-11-12T16:35:47.225Z\">4.35pm <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Farr points out that not all the names of everyone travelling to Syria is known by the British authorities.&nbsp;</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-52825826e4b0f37bee4ff5be\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-11-12T16:34:51.834Z\">4.34pm <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Vaz asks if there is an increase in British citizens going abroad to fight? Farr says there is not an issue in Afghanistan and Iraq, but there &quot;certainly is&quot; an issue in Syria. This number may or may not be increasing - but it's definitely a problem. Exit checks and the &quot;e-borders&quot; tracking system might help, Farr says. The number involved is in the hundreds, Farr says. People are also travelling to Somalia, but not nearly in the numbers travelling to Syria. Syria is easy to get to - you travel to Turkey and then cross the border by land.&nbsp;</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-5282574ce4b07aa4168b4ab7\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-11-12T16:31:31.363Z\">4.31pm <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Austin asks if people know who they are going to &quot;link up with&quot; when they set off for Syria. Farr says they generally go and then find likeminded people once they're there.</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-5282570be4b0f37bee4ff5bd\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-11-12T16:28:56.712Z\">4.28pm <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Farr says he does not know off the top of his head how many people travelling to fight abroad had come back.&nbsp;</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-528256b1e4b0f37bee4ff5bb\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-11-12T16:27:35.073Z\">4.27pm <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Austin asks about people from the UK travelling to fight abroad. How many people fighting abroad have we helped come back? Why were the Somaliland authorities not asked to prosecute Mohamed?</p> <p>Farr says they didn't have the evidence, so they wanted to deport him - just like the UK would if the position was reversed.</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-52825650e4b0f37bee4ff5ba\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-11-12T16:26:16.043Z\">4.26pm <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Labour's Ian Austin asks if Mohamed could have absconded so easily if he had been relocated as he would have been under a control order.</p> <p>Farr says he's not convinced by this.&nbsp;</p> <p>Austin says when relocation orders were introduced, no one absconded. When that element was dropped, two people absconded.</p> <p>Farr says he's seen no evidence that relocation is the salient issue.&nbsp;</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-528255c9e4b07aa4168b4ab5\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-11-12T16:24:28.555Z\">4.24pm <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Qureshi asks what counter-terrorism role the Metropolitan police has overseas, and how much money that costs.</p> <p>Farr says the Met has to manage a counter-terrorism network of officers overseas, in high-priority countries.&nbsp;</p> <p>Qureshi asks for an example.</p> <p>Farr says in Pakistan the UK is helping their judicial system collect evidence on terrorism suspects. It's been very successful, he says.&nbsp;</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-528254fbe4b07aa4168b4ab4\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-11-12T16:20:18.399Z\">4.20pm <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Had anyone else on control orders or Tpims absconded from a mosque,&nbsp;Yasmin Qureshi asks.&nbsp;</p> <p>Farr says he'd have to check.</p> <p>Qureshi says she's sure that if they had done the media would have mentioned it.&nbsp;</p> </div> <p class=\"block-time updated-time\">Updated <time datetime=\"2013-11-12T17:21:12.027Z\">at 5.21pm GMT</time></p> </div> <div id=\"block-5282542ee4b0f37bee4ff5b9\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-11-12T16:15:59.136Z\">4.15pm <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Vaz points out that Friday prayers taking place &quot;in congregation&quot; is very important for Muslims.</p> <p>Farr says the police would have to take a view.&nbsp;</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-528253dee4b0f37bee4ff5b8\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-11-12T16:15:18.523Z\">4.15pm <span class=\"timezone\">GMT</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Vaz asks how many of the many mosques in the country Tpim subjects will be banned from. Farr says there are 1,600 mosques in the UK.</p> <p>Farr says the mosques people would be banned from would be different for each Tpim subject.</p> </div> <p class=\"block-time updated-time\">Updated <time datetime=\"2013-11-12T17:20:54.947Z\">at 5.20pm GMT</time></p> </div> <div id=\"block-528253bbe4b07aa4168b4ab1\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-t